SIMPLE: likelihood
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Likelihood
<hw>Like"li*hood</hw> <pr>(l⟦imac⟧k"l⟦icr⟧*h⟦oocr⟧d)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Likely</ets> + <ets>-hood</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Appearance; show; sign; expression.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What of his heart perceive you in his face⟦br⟧
By any <qex>likelihood</qex> he showed to-day ?</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Likeness; resemblance.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There is no <qex>likelihood</qex> between pure light and black
darkness, or between righteousness and reprobation.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Raleigh.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Appearance of truth or reality; probability;
verisimilitude.</def> <rj><au>Tennyson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Statistical probability; probability of being true
or of occurring in the future; <as>as, the <ex>likelihood</ex> of being
abducted by aliens is close to zero.</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Likeliness</ent>⟦br⟧
